criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Pulmonary tuberculosis with completed treatment (patients that received at least six
             months of treatment and with confirmed cure by negative culture and/or sputum smear,
             or clinical and radiological improvement after well succeed treatment);

          -  Treatment finalized at least one year before.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Physically impaired to perform the functional tests;

          -  Coexisting lung pathology (history of previous respiratory disease or clinical or
             radiological evidence of lung disease other than tuberculosis);

          -  Pregnants.
